&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse  (Community Clinical)&lt;br /&gt;Permanent - Various Hours available&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NE Quadrant (Louth &amp; Skegness)     &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£23,607 per annum (negotialble dependant on experience &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;_________________________________________________________&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a vacancy for a Staff Nurse to join our established NE Community Services Team. You will be providing high quality palliative and end of life care in the community setting, supporting patients who have complex symptom management issues including the provision of emotional and psychological support, working as part of a highly skilled team. Core hours of the service are 8am to 4pm 7 days / week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We can provide the following opportunities for development:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preceptorship &amp; mentoring, as well as access to clinical supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dying to Communicate  &amp; Advance Care Planning Courses completed within 12 months&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical skills training and updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for further advanced development in specialist palliative skills &amp; academic development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications are welcome from candidates with:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current First Level registration with the NMC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to perform the role with empathy and consideration for the needs of patients and their families.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to adapt effectively to varying levels of demand as driven by patient needs or as directed by the line manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to independent transport to visit patients in their own homes is essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract:&lt;/strong&gt; Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:&lt;/strong&gt; Full and Part Time hours available up to 37.5 hours / week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; £23,607 - £29,595 pro rata dependent on skills and experience (plus weekend unsocial hours enhancement of 30% and contributory pension scheme or continuation of NHS pension)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Buying and selling of annual leave and lease car schemes are options available to qualifying new employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details or to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Ryan Jewitt, Senior Clinical Service Manager on 07767 167364 or by email on ryan.jewitt@stbarnabashospice.co.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To apply for this position please complete the online application process via NHS Jobs website.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For assistance please contact - recruitment@stbarnabashospice.co.uk &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note we do not accept CV’s only completed application forms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Barnabas Hospice is an Equal Opportunities Employer it believes in treating everyone with dignity and respect and encourages applications from all sectors of the community.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We reserve the right to extend, withdraw or close vacancies where necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that if you are selected for an interview you will be contacted via the email account you used to register on this site. Please check your spam folder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 22nd November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews to be arranged&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;___________________________________________________&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
